.TH "sys_rt_sigaction" 9 "sys_rt_sigaction" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sys_rt_sigaction \- alter an action taken by a process
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" sys_rt_sigaction
.BI "(int sig "  ","
.BI "const struct sigaction __user * act "  ","
.BI "struct sigaction __user * oact "  ","
.BI "size_t sigsetsize "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sig" 12
signal to be sent
.IP "act" 12
new sigaction
.IP "oact" 12
used to save the previous sigaction
.IP "sigsetsize" 12
size of sigset_t type
